dwm - dynamic window manager
============================
dwm is an extremely fast, small, and dynamic window manager for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dwm you need the Xlib header files.

Patches
-------
dwm-fixborders-6.2.diff  
dwm-noborderfloatingfix-6.2.diff  
dwm-pertag-20200914-61bb8b2.diff  
dwm-preserveonrestart-6.3.diff  
dwm-restartsig-20180523-6.2.diff  
dwm-moveresize-6.2.diff

Customizations
--------------
- added keybind to reset number of master clients to nmaster
- added keybind to reset size of master and stack split to mfact
- show master number in []= when not equal to nmaster
- replace M in [M] with number of clients when over 1
- made the window title color always show despite that monitor not
being focused

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dwm is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dwm (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install
